The paper discusses consensus protocols, which are commonly used in distributed systems and fall under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes using the network data plane to accelerate consensus, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses optimizing execution at the replicas, which falls under the category of Operating Systems (cs.OS) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance improvements achieved by the proposed approach, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
